				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Fine X does not increment. It specifies the tap off a delay line for pixels coming out of the shift register: 0 maximum delay, 7 minimum delay. If fine X is 7, and $2005 first write is written again with the same coarse X and fine X of 0, then the 7 most recently rendered background pixels will be rendered again.<br /><br />See also <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=14541" class="postlink">attempts to explain fine X to a non-native speaker roughly a year ago</a>.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

