				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">At any time, the PPU always has at least 8 pixels of the scanline ready to go to the screen, those 8 pixels are in a buffer, and fineX determines which of those 8 pixels is sent to the screen. However, after a pixel is drawn, instead of fineX increasing by one, the <em>contents of the buffer itself</em> are shifted over by one. By changing fineX in the middle of a scanline, it'll look like you're just skipping forward or skipping back.<br /><br />Another important thing to keep in mind is that sprites are actually offset by one pixel downwards. That means, if the game places a sprite at (X, Y), it will physically appear at (X, Y+1), and that does indeed affect the sprite 0 test.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

